The paper discusses joint learning of neural networks across multiple datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on tasks related to image classification, auto-encoders, and image generation, which are all subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques to determine how layers should be shared between datasets, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of their approach on three tasks, which suggests that it may fall under the subfield of natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
